SCHMALLENBERG VIRUS - EUROPE (74): INTERNATIONAL TRADE, UPDATE
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
[1] Russia ex Austria
[2] Ireland update
[3] Germany update
[4] UK update

******
[1] Russia ex Austria
Date: Mon 3 Dec 2012
Source: Rosselkhoznadzor, Russia's Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance/Press about us [machine trans. edited]
http://fsvps.ru/fsvps/press/3289.html, from http://www.furazh.ru/ (Fodder online)


Laboratory tests performed on blood samples collected from 224 head of Austrian cattle imported into Abansky district of the Krasnoyarsk region revealed the presence of antibodies against the Schmallenberg virus [SBV]. This indicates that the animals had been infected by the virus previously, Rosselkhoznadzor reported. Currently, the animals are being examined for the presence of the live virus.

Rosselkhoznadzor notified cattle importers of cattle from the EU that such imports may be related to added risk in case live virus is detected. This may lead to the requirement of the destruction of the animals or their re-exportation; the latter is not always possible, for technical reasons.

In addition, Rosselkhoznadzor informed importers that in the near future, a decision may be taken to discontinue the imports of breeding cattle from countries where the SBV disease has spread in view of the fact that guarantees provided to Rosselkhoznadzor by national veterinary services of the EU concerning the SBV health status of such animals have not always been satisfactory.

